Here's the XAML and ViewModel setup:

**XAML**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false;  // stops the spinner
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync(nameof(DetailPage), new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", CurrentItem }
        });
        CurrentItem = null;  // reset so user can re-select same item
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| Property | Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `TwoWay` (default on RefreshView) | Controls the refresh spinner; set `false` when done |
| `Command` on RefreshView | `RefreshCommand` | Fires your API reload logic |
| `SelectedItem` | `CurrentItem`, `Mode=TwoWay` | Tracks the selected item; reset to `null` after navigation |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Triggers navigation to the detail page |
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | **Must** be `ObservableCollection`, not `List`, so add/remove updates the UI |

**Important notes:**
- Always set `IsRefreshing = false` when refresh completes, or the spinner stays visible.
- Reset `CurrentItem = null` after navigation so the same item can be re-selected.
- Update the collection on the **UI thread** via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
- Use `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings. Never use `ViewCell`.
